## 6. Technical Architecture

### 6.1 Frontend Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **React Native** (Expo) | Cross-platform mobile framework |
| **TypeScript** | Type-safe codebase |
| **Expo Router / React Navigation** | Tab + stack navigation |
| **AsyncStorage** | Local data persistence (free/Pro users) |
| **i18next** | Internationalization (5 languages + RTL) |
| **Lucide React Native** | Icon library |
| **date-fns** | Date formatting & calculations |
| **react-native-view-shot** | Screenshot capture for Aura sharing |
| **expo-sharing** | Native share sheet integration |

### 6.2 Backend & Cloud Services

| Service | Purpose | Cost Implications |
|---|---|---|
| **Convex** | Real-time cloud database, serverless functions, mutations/queries | Per-usage pricing |
| **OpenAI API** (GPT-5.1 + GPT-4o-mini) | AI Chat + Workout Aura generation | Per-token pricing, optimized with smart model routing |
| **Clerk** | User authentication (sign up, sign in, account deletion) | Per-MAU pricing |
| **RevenueCat** | In-app purchase management, entitlement tracking, subscription analytics | Revenue-share or flat pricing |
| **EAS (Expo Application Services)** | Build, submit, and OTA updates | Expo pricing |

### 6.3 Database Schema (Convex)

| Table | Description |
|---|---|
| `users` | User profiles (Clerk ID, name, email, DOB, gender, weight, height, body fat, goal) |
| `workouts` | Workout sessions (name, timestamps, notes, mood, aura data) |
| `exerciseLogs` | Exercise entries within a workout (exercise name, superset group, order) |
| `sets` | Individual sets within an exercise log (weight, reps, RPE, type) |
| `customExercises` | User-created exercises |
| `personalRecords` | PRs (max weight, best volume, estimated 1RM) |
| `bodyMeasurements` | Body measurements over time (7 body parts) |

---

## 7. Key Differentiators & Competitive Advantages

| Advantage | Details |
|---|---|
| **AI-Powered Coaching** | Not just a logger — the AI has full access to the user's data and gives personalized, data-driven advice. Uses dynamic model routing to optimize cost. |
| **Workout Aura** | Unique, viral-ready, shareable post-workout cards with humor. 3 character modes. Designed for social media sharing (Instagram Stories, etc.). Strong organic growth potential. |
| **Reverse Trial Model** | Users get the full Pro experience for 14 days with zero friction. Higher conversion than traditional free-with-upsell. |
| **Hybrid Offline/Online** | Works fully offline for free/Pro users (AsyncStorage). AI subscribers get cloud sync. No internet dependency for core features. |
| **Multi-Language + RTL** | 5 languages including Arabic with full RTL — targets Middle East and South Asian markets underserved by competitors. |
| **One-Time Purchase Option** | Unlike competitors that force subscriptions, RepAI offers a $4.99 lifetime option. Appeals to subscription-fatigued users. |
| **Superset/Circuit Support** | Visual grouping of exercises into supersets, circuits, and giant sets — a feature missing from many competitors. |
| **Personal Record Detection** | Automatic PR detection with celebration animations — gamification that drives engagement. |
| **Low Entry Barrier** | No account required to use the app. Account only needed for AI features. |

